  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He-- he was an Jewish-- I don't want to say intellectual, but he was an well-educated young man, which made it-- which made it his business to run or supervise those Jewish children which came to the [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] JUL, came to this building, which was set up by the Jewish community as an recreational center for the children, for the Jewish children, so the children are not always at home.",
      "word_count": 73
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they couldn't be on the streets, so they should be in certain classrooms.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Aron Menczer had the idea of teaching them, first of all, Judaism, because most of those children were like me, from assimilated families.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was the first time when we heard about Jewish songs; when we learned how to dance the  hora, a traditional Jewish dance; when we heard about Jewish writers; or when we heard about the history of immigration into Palestine, the first [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] building of kibbutzim.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he slowly introduced us to the idea of Zionism.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was instrumental in creating a garden, or taking over a garden, which was owned by Rothschild in the outskirts of Vienna, and made a small beginning of a hachshara.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hachshara is an-- is the idea of group teaching children or teenagers how to live from the land, which means work in the garden, produce vegetables, have perhaps a cow, how to milk a cow, which was very strange for us.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And by the way, the vegetables produced in this particular garden went to the Jewish hospital called Billroth Hospital in Vienna, and where we actually did productive work because of that.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In the meantime, many things happened.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Suddenly I found out an uncle or an aunt were gone.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were just emigrating to Australia.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
